cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on image classification using large convolutional networks and leverages semi-supervised learning with a teacher/student paradigm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the success factors and recommendations for producing high-accuracy models, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of unlabelled images for video classification, which could potentially fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and the use of fine-grained classification, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
